@node install "Installation"
@{jcenter}@{u}@{b}Installation@{ub}@{uu}
@{jleft}	Pretty simple. Find the one with the CPU type you need (020, 030, etc),
rename it to "AmiStatus", and drop it into your Sys:wbstartup drawer (if you want it to
launch every time you boot, otherwise, just put it wherever you like). The status_pics
folder contains some useful "icon pictures", mostly sniped from the Tangoish Linux icon
pack (would credit the author, but I can't remember who s/he is. On my to-do for next
u/l). A few other icons in there, too. Have online/offline Facebook icons (For jabber
chat clients), Privoxy, and anything else I forgot about. The included scripts in the
rexx drawer might look for these in presets:status_pics/, but this can be changed in
the scripts. Also, the example scripts are designed to be put in their appropriate
program's AREXX or REXX directories.

@endnode

